The paper deals with multiple description coding for a Gaussian source, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses lossless multi-level diversity source coding, which falls under the category of source coding (cs.SI). The use of polytopes and bounding techniques suggests a connection to optimization and algorithms (cs.DS), while the extension to general sources suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
